Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a probably Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium red-brown; some mica. Rectangular stamp with prow symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 56, 17 or 122, 32? Name Sosikrates.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0256)
